cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper proposes a deep learning architecture for mapping GPR B-Scan data to complex permittivity maps of subsurface structures, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks (NN) for inversion, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE. The paper also discusses the use of synthetic data for training the model, which is a common topic in the sub-category of cs.AI. Finally, the paper involves the use of signal processing techniques for GPR data, which is related to the sub-category of cs.IR.
